test.name: Test Case 1: Login with invalid email on the web custom app

kw.name: Main Web Setup
Empty Directory
kw.doc: Deletes all the content from the given directory.

kw.name: Set Screenshot Directory
kw.doc: Sets the directory where screenshots are saved.

kw.name: Open Browser
kw.doc: Opens a new browser instance to the optional ``url``.

kw.name: Maximize Browser Window
kw.doc: Maximizes current browser window.
This is the main setup for the connexi

kw.name: GIVEN I go to web login page
Go To
kw.doc: Navigates the current browser window to the provided ``url``.

kw.name: Wait Until Page Contains
kw.doc: Waits until ``text`` appears on the current page.

kw.name: Input Text
kw.doc: Types the given ``text`` into the text field identified by ``locator``.

kw.name: Input Text
kw.doc: Types the given ``text`` into the text field identified by ``locator``.

kw.name: Click Element
kw.doc: Click the element identified by ``locator``.

kw.name: THEN Message should display in web
Page Should Contain
kw.msg: Current page contains text 'Invalid username or password.'.
kw.doc: Verifies that current page contains ``text``.

kw.name: Main Web Teardown
Capture Page Screenshot
kw.doc: Takes a screenshot of the current page and embeds it into a log file.

kw.name: Close All Browsers
kw.doc: Closes all open browsers and resets the browser cache.
This is the main teardown for the web app

kw.name: Open Application
kw.doc: Opens a new application to given Appium server. Capabilities of appium server, Android and iOS, Please check https://appium.io/docs/en/2.1/cli/args/ | *Option* | *Man.* | *Description* | | remote_url | Yes | Appium server url | | alias | no | alias | | strict_ssl | No | allows you to send commands to an invalid certificate host like a self-signed one. |
This is the main setup for the kadena mobile app

kw.name: GIVEN I navigate to mobile login page
Wait Until Element Is Visible

kw.name: Input Text
